                                                                                                               Birla Corp lines up funds for expansion
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Calcutta, May 7: The board of Birla Corporation Ltd  the flagship of the MP Birla group  has approved a Rs 500-crore expansion plan to increase capacity to 10 million tonnes.        
	The company, whose turnover crossed Rs 2,000 crore in the last fiscal, at present operates at 5.8mt capacity. The board had earlier approved the expansion of the capacity of existing plants to 7.5mt by March 2010.        
	Besides cement, the board cleared two power plants, one coal washery and a waste heat recovery plant, which will cost another Rs 400 crore.        
	Profit rise        
	Birla Corp has posted an operating profit of Rs 501.93 crore in 2008-09, against Rs 614.33 crore a year ago. The net profit and earning per share was Rs 323.51 crore and Rs 42.01, respectively.         
	The company declared a dividend of Rs 4.50 per share.         
	For the quarter ended March 31, 2009, it registered a turnover of Rs 630.16 crore, against Rs 563.14 crore a year ago. The net profit was higher at Rs 90.61 crore, against Rs 86.56 crore a year ago, mainly on account of a better demand for cement from the governments infrastructure and rural projects.                                                                                                                                       
